=\"async\" width=\"1700\" height=\"2438\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02.jpg\" alt=\"A sculptural steel arbour frames the Phoenix Rooftop garden in central Melbourne, casting dynamic shadows across a mosaic-tiled courtyard. The space blends lush planting, custom tiling, and defined seating zones to create a liveable garden 30 storeys above the city. This rooftop retreat shows how structure and greenery can work together in high-rise outdoor design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02.jpg 1700w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02-940x1348.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02-800x1147.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02-768x1101.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02-1071x1536.jpg 1071w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-02-1428x2048.jpg 1428w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1700px) 100vw, 1700px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt 30 storeys, this is one of the highest rooftop gardens in Melbourne. The site’s exposure required careful consideration of wind, drainage, and plant selection. For BENT Architecture, the goal was not only to deliver environmental performance, but to create a space that could be used and enjoyed daily.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03.jpg\" alt=\"A sculptural steel arbour frames the Phoenix Rooftop garden in central Melbourne, casting dynamic shadows across a mosaic-tiled courtyard. The space blends lush planting, custom tiling, and defined seating zones to create a liveable garden 30 storeys above the city. This rooftop retreat shows how structure and greenery can work together in high-rise outdoor design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-03-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe rooftop is divided into three distinct but connected zones. One supports standing and circulation, another is designed for sitting and relaxing, and a third is used for outdoor dining. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1266\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-04.jpg\" alt=\"A sculptural steel arbour frames the Phoenix Rooftop garden in central Melbourne, casting dynamic shadows across a mosaic-tiled courtyard. The space blends lush planting, custom tiling, and defined seating zones to create a liveable garden 30 storeys above the city. This rooftop retreat shows how structure and greenery can work together in high-rise outdoor design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-04.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-04