-landscaping-plants-270525-714-08-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-08-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-08-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-08-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eVisible from surrounding office buildings, the garden also serves as a reminder of what is possible in dense urban settings. It adds a layer of visual greenery to the city and invites further exploration into how rooftop spaces can support both ecological and social goals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1707\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09.jpg\" alt=\"A sculptural steel arbour frames the Phoenix Rooftop garden in central Melbourne, casting dynamic shadows across a mosaic-tiled courtyard. The space blends lush planting, custom tiling, and defined seating zones to create a liveable garden 30 storeys above the city. This rooftop retreat shows how structure and greenery can work together in high-rise outdoor design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09.jpg 1707w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09-940x1410.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-09-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe garden reveals plants cascading over custom mosaic-tiled planters. The small-scale tiles in green, yellow, cream, and deep blue tones add texture and visual rhythm, contrasting with the soft, flowering greenery. This detail showcases how BENT Architecture integrated planting and hardscape to create a functional, visually rich rooftop space.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1400\" height=\"2099\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10.jpg\" alt=\"Trailing rosemary spills over a mosaic-tiled planter on Melbourne\u0026#39;s Phoenix Rooftop, blending hardscape and greenery in a striking vertical detail. The mix of green, cream, yellow, and deep blue tiles adds texture and movement, while the flowering herbs soften the structure and provide sensory appeal. A perfect example of how to create depth and character in rooftop garden design.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10.jpg 1400w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/rooftop-garden-landscaping-plants-270525-714-10-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"